{"sha": "3a1ffead36232a759a4dbdc72a5302a8f8722605", "node_id": "C_kwDOAAsO6NoAKDNhMWZmZWFkMzYyMzJhNzU5YTRkYmRjNzJhNTMwMmE4Zjg3MjI2MDU", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Simon Chopin", "email": "simon.chopin@canonical.com", "date": "2022-02-11T09:20:32Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Simon Chopin", "email": "simon.chopin@canonical.com", "date": "2022-02-11T09:45:59Z"}, "message": "linkchecker: fix panic on directory symlinks\n\nIn Debian and Ubuntu, there are some patches that change the rustc/fonts\ndirectory to a symlink to the system fonts. This triggers a latent bug\nin linkchecker, as the DirEntry filetype isn't a dir but later on the\nfile itself, when opened, is one, triggering an unreachable!() clause.\n\nThis patch fixes the situation by using std::fs::metadata, which goes\nthrough symlinks.\n\nI'd have added a test case but `tidy` doesn't seem to like symlinks, and\nmoreover I'm not sure how Git deals with symlinks on Windows.\n\nSigned-off-by: Simon Chopin <simon.chopin@canonical.com>", "tree": {"sha": "18281a91d6618b2fc36993f97bd711d9f2336458", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/18281a91d6618b2fc36993f97bd711d9f2336458"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/3a1ffead36232a759a4dbdc72a5302a8f8722605", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/3a1ffead36232a759a4dbdc72a5302a8f8722605", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/3a1ffead36232a759a4dbdc72a5302a8f8722605", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/3a1ffead36232a759a4dbdc72a5302a8f8722605/comments", "author": {"login": "schopin-pro", "id": 87005181, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg3MDA1MTgx", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/87005181?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schopin-pro", "html_url": "https://github.com/schopin-pro", "followers_ur